<big>1996. The [[Caius Taggert|Party Host]] stands in the desolation of his citadel in the centre of the [[Level Fun/The Party Rooms|Party Rooms]]. 

He is alone. The old Co-Hosts are dead at the hands of [[The Party Pooper|the man who had become his arch-nemesis]], and he has not yet chosen new ones to fill their empty sockets. Sockets? Positions. He means ''positions''. 

On that fateful day, a visitant arrives, clothed all in grey, the lights flickering as he manifests into being. 

"<span class="caius-text">Who are you?</span>" asks the Party Host. 

"<span class="juju-text">I am thy Reckoning, Caius,</span>" says the spectre, "<span class="juju-text">I am thy Alpha and thy Omega.</span>"

"<span class="caius-text">No, you're not Him,</span>" returns Sir Caius, "<span class="caius-text">You cannot be Him.</span>"

"<span class="juju-text">Explain this, then,</span>" the visitant answers, and with the flourish of a key he reveals a young [[Entity 9|faceling]] girl with only one eye, seemingly from thin air. 

Sir Caius pauses, his eye widening. "<span class="caius-text">But... but that's... you're [[Maria|Tobias's daughter]]...? What devilry is this?</span>"

"<span class="juju-text">Providence, not devilry,</span>" replies the vistant calmly. "<span class="juju-text">''Vous ne pouvez cacher vos péchés aux yeux de Notre-Dame, Caius.''</span>"

"<span class="caius-text">What... what sins?</span>"

And the spirit declares, "<span class="juju-text">Do not act as if thou knowst not what I speak of. This pure, innocent girl is just one of the thousands of innocent thou hast killed, or caused to be killed. Thy salvation is less than visible, Caius... Thou hast but one option left.</span>"

For one time in his life of power and control, the Party Host feels a twinge of fear for his immortal soul.  "<span class="caius-text">''Beata Maria,''</span>" he says softly, looking upon the faceling child, "<span class="caius-text">I must... hail Mary.</span>"

"<span class="juju-text">Treat her well, and perhaps, just perhaps, all will be forgiven,</span>" says the visitant. He raises a key from his belt and turns to leave. 

"<span class="caius-text">... Yes, Lord.</span>"

The spectre turns his head slightly backwards, and smiles cruelly. 

"<span class="juju-text">I am not your Lord, Caius. Nothing even close to it. I am just like you: vainglorious, manipulative, and chaotic.</span>"

Sir Caius pauses again. "<span class="caius-text">What?</span>"

"<span class="juju-text">Your promise is binding. Break it, and it is not I who will decide your punishment, but [[Boundless Torturer|Fate]] itself.</span>"

And with that, the Party Host awakens from his dream into waking life. The Juju Man has vanished, but [[Maria]] is still there. 
</big>

























