Made partially for my canon, partially to explain the mystery of the "Keyman" on [[Maria]]'s page. Vague inspirations of varying vagueness from the BFG, Epiales (the Greek spirit of nightmares), Sauron, <span class="basic-tooltip" title="Yes I'm comparing Caius to Frollo">the Archdeacon from ''Hunchback of Notre-Dame''</span>, and <span class="basic-tooltip" title="This is NOT a Keymaster rewrite">the Keymaster</span>. 

To clarify — the Juju Man is indeed from [[the Broken]], and due to the nature of that dimension, he does not truly possess what is called a ''genuine existence''; he is non-existent. Imprisonment and freedom (represented here by keys) are a ''key'' motif of my canon, but more than this I cannot say. And as for that final section, [[Caius Taggert]] was conned not once but twice — he will receive no cosmic retribution from the [[Boundless Torturer]] if he breaks his promise, for the Juju Man is not real, and therefore the promise was never real either.  
